{"TopicId":179252,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Reaction wheel perpetual spin","CreatedByName":"Zosma Procyon","CreatedById":151656,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T19:52:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Zosma Procyon","CreatedById":151656,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T19:52:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to set reaction wheels to keep spinning until shutdown after they\u0027re detached from the main vehicle, like for instance if you were using then to drive a propeller?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T20:06:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PrvDancer85","CreatedById":180954,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T20:28:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbecore and trim?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems to work for me, isnt that how they do the fancy stockprobs?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-24T20:50:09Z\u0022 title=\u002210/24/2018 08:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 24, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by PrvDancer85\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-24T21:09:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223474677\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179252\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540410752\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151656\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zosma Procyon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Zosma Procyon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to set reaction wheels to keep spinning until shutdown after they\u0027re detached from the main vehicle, like for instance if you were using then to drive a propeller?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes there is: like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/180954-prvdancer85/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022180954\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/180954-prvdancer85/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@PrvDancer85\u003C/a\u003E mentions, you need to add a probe core so it can be controlled when detached. Then once detached, make sure \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is off and set a trim for the axis you want the spin on. Eg. for a propeller with a probe core in the direction of the shaft, hold Alt-E or Alt-Q for a sustained spin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-13T23:01:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223474690\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179252\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540411610\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/24/2018 at 10:06 PM, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot in stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes you want\u00A0Firespitter for serious propeller planes, the probe ones are just for fun and doing it stock exploit then you can have an Kerbal on an ladder escape from eve \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}